"We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks."

messages.text: Amazing! btw. How is it possible for YLD APP to give such high rewards? Its not just money comes out of thin air. I always wondered about these reward programs...Is there any article that explains the logic behind those rewards?

"We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks."

I participated heavily in SwissBorg ICO and it turned out to be a good decision so far. SwissBorg is a great project, with a good team and ethics. Their app is very nice and has a great UX. Big advantage I see in the fiat rails they have for different currencies. And especially I like their smart engine for coin exchange very much. They also have a USDC yield, the highest rate was at 30% APY, the last few days it was around 15%. As well they have a smart yield for their own token. The tokenomics are grat. By locking CHSB for premium and yield, the free supply on the market went down drastically and this scarcity is a big point that makes the price go up. As well they have a protect & burn mechanism for their token. And the safety net for USDC yield is held in CHSB. BTC, ETH and BNB yield should be released soon. 

So there would be a lot more to tell, but this should be a basic info on SwissBorg. 

It took SwissBorg almost 3 years since their ICO to launch their WealthApp. So my opinion is that they are slow with developing. As well ETH / BTC yield was not released yet and users wait a long time for it. So they are kind of slow in new releases. 

Yield app on the other hand launched in November / Dezember and they are developing fast IMHO. As well they offer the highest yields in theindustry, which is fantastic. Of course they are "behind" SwissBorg with development, because they launched just some months ago. But if they can bring frequent releases they should be able to possibly catch up. 

An other point is that SwissBorg is focussing on the European market. They will not enter US market due to difficult regulations. The team at Yield app seem to have more experience in finance and FinTech and could be able to enter US market which would be huge. So since Yield app is sitting at CMC 350 they have massive room to grow. If they keep delivering and with the great team they have I see Yield as a potential serious competitor to SwissBorg, Voyager and even Celsius. üöÄ

text: Some info about this, by our CEO:

text.text:
"We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks."

text: You can see some of our CEO's thoughts on the matter, here:

text.text:
We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamentals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. On the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.
 
YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.
 
Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory.  As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.
 
To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.
 
We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.
 
The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks.

Depends on the country. Mining, staking, and interests are taxable the moment a user receives, in many countries.
For what country?

Perhaps in your country.

In mine, as soon as I earn an asset the dollar value of the asset accrues as its fiat value at the time of acquisition.

If it later devalues. You have a problem.

You owe income tax on the assets value, and if you sell it later for a profit you accrue capital gains on the difference.

Or a capital loss to carry forward if you sell for a loss later on.

As the two taxes are seperate, having a write off on gains does not offset any income liability.
You talking about UK?
Yes.
Not a single reference in the UK goverment page in relation to crypto currency in terms of paying tax until you withdraw into your account as fiat
Once you withdraw into your fiat account you pay capital gains 10% for interest gains and you pay 20% for mining, staking, airdrops, day trading
I suggest you do better research for your own sake sir.

Capital Gains Tax

HMRC would expect that buying and selling of cryptoassets by an individual will normally amount to investment activity (rather than a trade of dealing in cryptoassets). In such cases, if an individual invests in cryptoassets they will typically have to pay¬†Capital Gains Tax¬†on any gains they realise.

Cryptoassets are digital and therefore intangible, but count as a ‚Äòchargeable asset‚Äô for Capital Gains Tax if they‚Äôre both:

capable of being owned

have a value that can be realised

What constitutes a ‚Äòdisposal‚Äô

Individuals need to calculate their gain or loss when they dispose of their cryptoassets to find out whether they need to pay Capital Gains Tax. A ‚Äòdisposal‚Äô is a broad concept and includes:

selling cryptoassets for money

exchanging cryptoassets for a different type of cryptoasset

using cryptoassets to pay for goods or services

giving away cryptoassets to another person
Exchanging crypto assets for a different type is a taxable event.

text: Many places, I'd suggest giving a read to our whitepaper, it goes into depth in this and other topics related to the platform, here:

A little excerpt from page 4 might help with your question:

"...Decentralized Finance: the next big thing in FinTech is already hereIn recent years, decentralized finance (DeFi) has emerged as the most exciting innovation in FinTech. DeFi solutions rely on smart contracts and blockchain technology to deliver financial instruments that are mutualized, peer-to-peer, permissionless, and fully automated. These can be assembled into even more complex solutions to further drive rapid innovation. DeFi solutions currently fall into a few prominent categories. These include:

‚Ä¢ Prediction Markets (Gnosis and Augur)
‚Ä¢ Collateralized Lending (Aave)
‚Ä¢ Collateralized Stable Assets (DAI)
‚Ä¢ Automated Market Makers (Uniswap, Balancer)
‚Ä¢ Derivatives (Synthetix and Opyn)

messages.text: Ok.. But will I get airdrop anyway, if I was staking with Trustswap for months, even if I didnt participate in Yield token sale or I dont have acc yet?
How can you offer yields of up to 20%? Is that sustainable?

We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks.

Hello, Can somebody explain me how it works I mean so high APY on stablecoins, when banks give you nothing?

We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks.

We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks.

It's an ETH erc-20 address you're depositing to. When you deposit through e.g. Ledger Live or metamask just don't change the gas limit. You only tweak the gwei for gas to make sure the tx goes through within the timeframe you want it to go through. 

And don't forget there is a minimum amount of ETH you need to send to your Yield wallet, otherwise it won't show up.

I don't get why some of you have tx's that fail.
Trezor wallet has 21000 gas limit as default and other wallets too even you dont touch it
Metamask changes the gas limit by default (depending on market conditions, not on what you‚Äôre doing), and it seems hardware wallets don‚Äôt do that

what?
Metamask changes the gas limit based on the complexitity of the tx, not market conditions.. lol

Isn‚Äôt gas limit the maximum amount you can spend? It doesn‚Äôt matter if it‚Äôs a swap or a simple eth send, it just dictates what max you willing to pay for the transaction. In the early days, you could have swaps that were cheaper than today‚Äôs simple sends. Or am I wrong?

Gas limit is indeed the maximum amount of gas you can/will spend on the complexity of the tx, in order to make sure it's send to the network. 
On top of that you pay gas usually shown in gwei to adjust the speed of the tx to get mined inside a block. 

The gas limit is properly adjusted based on the complexity of the tx on metamask. You don't touch the gas limit unless you kn now what you're doing! 
You just tweak the gwei (gas) for speed adjustment.

Yeah, you normally only mess with the gwei to make sure your transaction goes smoothly. The thing is, the gas limit can also dictate if a miner is or isn‚Äôt going to pick up your transaction to do the work, seeing as even with a high gwei, your transaction might fail because he didn‚Äôt get ‚Äúpaid‚Äù enough

In very very rare cases you adjust the gas limit if you need to set it manually if the default is wrong and the tx is more complex the what the gas limit can handle. But usually this is shared by devs of project and it's very rare you do this. 

I think most people have still no idea what the hell they're doing and how ethereum works. This is basic stuff.
haha of course not! How did you get to this conclusion?
It isn‚Äôt? Might have had the wrong understanding then!!
Gas limit is ONLY paid for the complexity of the tx. You can set it as high as you want but the tx will still use only what it requires!

Try it out sometime! 

Look at one of your tx's on Etherscan. 
you see that there is an ESTIMATION and then there is the ACTUAL fees paid.
Yeah yeah, I mean if you set it too low! üòÅ

Well, how about you just don't touch it. 
Like I said, the gas limit should be fine per default as it picks up the complexity of the smart contract. 

Just don't touch the gas limit, and only tweak the gwei for gas paid as part of the speed.

Okay a few things.
1. I can not emphasize how important it is to do your research on gas, how it works etc. It does not make any sense to commit transactions if you have no idea how the mechanism of gas works.
You're bound to pay a lot more than you intend and you'll probably end up with transactions not going through, while you pay gas anyway.  The ethereum network doesn't care if the tx is successful or failed. You ALWAYS pay gas when you send a tx to the network.

I know. I received $20 worth Matic for winning one of their twitter giveaway and since then this txn is on hold. I wanted to move it to Celsius but it can't be done unless I move them to ethereum network. Those $20 are now worth $350. So, trying to get them out of Matic network now
Wait, let me get my laptop and type this out.
Ok

Ethereum tx's at their base exist out of two parts. 
1. Gas limit
2. Gas price

Gas limit is set for the complexity of the tx. 
Not all transactions are equally complex and require the same amoung of computational power. E.g. a tx from your Ledger eth 1 wallet to your Ledger eth 2 wallet probably requires a 21000 gas limit (simple tx). But a swap on Uniswap requires more because it probably needs to convert the crypto into wETH and then convert to the desired crypto. If you're claiming or adding liquidity to a pool for example, the gas limit is also much higher since these are all complex type of tx's and require more computational power. 

So, this is why we do NOT change the gas limit. It's 99% shown with the correct amount required to make sure the tx goes through.

Another thing about the gas limit is that you can set it as high as you want. Yes,,, You can set it as high as you want!!!! It doesn't matter, because the tx will only use what is required (e.g. 21000 for a simple tx) and the rest will not be deducted from your wallet. 

In very rare cases we change the gas limit. Usually the developer of the smart contract has already set the gas limit for each type of tx, so that you get it correct by default!

text:
2. Gas price is meant for speed of the tx. So if you want it to go through faster, you set it higher. If you want lower fees, you should check the gas fees on various sites, compare them and see what works for you / how much time you are willing to wait.
-
- Etc. --> do your own research

can anyone tell me how they are paying 10% on YLD token? where is the yield coming from? if its coming from treasury it is surely only a short term arrangement as thats not sustainable

We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. the first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks.

messages.text:
Hi Seneca. We‚Äôre being asked this question now and then, and here is how YIELD App views the sustainability of the APY offered: 

We see DeFi as a sustainable industry built on solid fundamanetals. We see 10% as sustainable long term and we can securely offer above this. The first instance and within the current macro climate, we can generate Alpha through economies of scale. By aggregating capital and employing technology solutions to compliment the portfolio team, YIELD App is in a position to profit from trading strategies that are not available to individual or market participants with insufficient capital reserves. 

Examples of this may include priority access to protocol testnets and in turn as a primary liquidity provider to new protocols in mainnet.

YIELD App‚Äôs portfolio allocations are diversified across multiple strategies and trading opportunities; these can include automated funding rate arbitrage and asset disposals through our proprietary portfolio management system that is able to identify the highest yielding market opportunities and process these through YIELD App‚Äôs internal risk analysis algorithms to generate instantaneous execution and transaction requests for digital approval (multi-sig) by our portfolio managers.

Outside of execution methodologies and tools, YIELD App believes that DeFi as a nascent asset class is only at the starting point of a multi-year growth trajectory. As with any new financial market innovation, it is inevitable that inefficiencies will be present; this is particularly amplified in the context of cryptocurrencies and the P2P nature of decentralized finance.

To that effect, it can be considered that the ‚ÄòRisk-Adjusted Rate of Return‚Äô, the trade-off between risk and expected returns or the risk premium that an investor demands for investment participation in decentralized financial instruments, will naturally be measured against other mature income generating financial instruments. We are seeing this today through the outsized returns (>1,000% APY) that can be achieved using complex liquidity mining strategies and re-hypothecation techniques.

We believe that our 10% APY will be sustainable in the long run due to these reasons, notwithstanding the inherent risk premium ascribed to cryptocurrency assets against a backdrop of perpetually low interest rates since the global financial crises, central bank fiscal loosening policies before and during the COVID-19 pandemic, and the dearth of high Income, low risk alternative assets classes available to non-sophisticated investors.

The minimum APY offered to YIELD users is nonetheless subject to change at the discretion of management and will be reviewed in line with broader market attributes and prevailing underlying benchmarks.

Two ways you can send from ethereum to avalanche. 
1. use the official avalanche bridge (the have a dedicated telegram channel for this)
2. Send it to e.g. Binance, exchange it for Avax. Send avax to your wallet (x-chain). Send from x-chain to c-chain. Send from c-chain to your metamask on your avalanche (avalanche mainnet on metamask).
